        <p>Perlick, True, Turbo Air, Beverage-Air — the brands that run LA bars. Keg coolers, back bar, bottle coolers</p>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="hero-badge-icon">📋</div>
        <h4>COI Available</h4>
        <p>Named to your building owner or management company — ready before we arrive</p>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="hero-badge-icon">⚡</div>
        <h4>Same Day Service</h4>
        <p>Weekday morning calls get same-day dispatch. Friday calls get moved to front of queue.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="trust-bar">
  <div class="trust-bar-inner">
    <div class="ti">🏅 BHGS #A49573</div>
    <div class="ti">🛡️ Fully Insured · COI Available</div>
    <div class="ti">⚡ Same Day Commercial Service</div>
    <div class="ti">🧊 Ice Machine Specialists</div>
    <div class="ti">💬 $120 Diagnostic — Waived With Repair</div>
  </div>
</div>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="two-col">
      <div class="body-text">
        <p class="sl">Bar & Nightclub Service</p>
        <h2>A broken ice machine at 4pm on a Friday is not a Monday problem</h2>
        <p>We get calls from bar managers and owners across LA in exactly that situation — equipment that failed at the worst possible time. The ice machine that stopped making ice Thursday night. The Perlick back bar refrigerator that's not holding temperature on a Saturday afternoon. The glasswasher that died before a private event.</p>
        <p>West Hollywood has one of the highest bar-per-square-mile densities in LA, and those bars run equipment hard — seven nights a week, long service windows, high volume. The ice machines in WeHo cocktail bars are running 18 hours a day during a busy week. LA's hard water creates scale buildup that kills ice production capacity faster than the manufacturer's quarterly cleaning schedule accounts for.</p>
        <p>We carry parts for the brands that actually run LA bars — Perlick, True, Turbo Air, Beverage-Air for refrigeration; Manitowoc, Hoshizaki, Scotsman for ice; Champion, Jackson, Hobart for glasswashers. Most WeHo and Silver Lake bar calls get resolved in one visit.</p>
        <p>Bars are one of the few businesses where every hour of downtime during service has a direct, calculable revenue number attached to it. We know that. We move accordingly on bar calls — especially when the call comes in on a Friday morning.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cta-box">
        <h3>Bar & Nightclub Service Line</h3>
        <p>Equipment down before service? Call now.</p>
        <a href="tel:+14243250520" class="cta-phone">☎ (424) 325-0520</a>
        <a href="/contact/" class="cta-book">Request Service Online</a>
        <p class="cta-note">Licensed · COI Available · No call center</p>
        <div class="price-mini">
          <div class="pm-row"><span class="pm-label">Commercial diagnostic</span><span class="pm-val">$120</span></div>
          <div class="pm-row"><span class="pm-label">Applied to repair</span><span class="pm-val">Yes</span></div>
          <div class="pm-row"><span class="pm-label">Parts on truck</span><span class="pm-val">Most brands</span></div>
          <div class="pm-row"><span class="pm-label">COI on request</span><span class="pm-val">Available</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">Equipment We Service</p>
    <h2>Behind the bar and in the back — full coverage</h2>
    <div class="equip-grid">
      <div class="equip-card">
        <div class="equip-icon">🧊</div>
        <h3>Commercial Ice Machines</h3>
        <p>Full-cube, half-cube, nugget, flake — all ice types. Scale buildup, harvest cycle failures, water valve issues. LA hard water descaling included.</p>
        <p class="equip-brands">Manitowoc · Hoshizaki · Scotsman · Ice-O-Matic</p>
      </div>
      <div class="equip-card">
        <div class="equip-icon">🍺</div>
        <h3>Bar Refrigerators & Keg Coolers</h3>
        <p>Back bar refrigerators, keg coolers, direct-draw draft systems, bottle coolers. Not cooling, temperature fluctuation, fan motor failures, door gasket wear.</p>
        <p class="equip-brands">Perlick · True · Turbo Air · Beverage-Air · Back Bar</p>
      </div>
      <div class="equip-card">
        <div class="equip-icon">🥃</div>
        <h3>Wine & Bottle Display Cases</h3>
        <p>Wine display refrigerators, bottle display cases, under-counter wine coolers. Temperature control failures, compressor issues, LED lighting.</p>
        <p class="equip-brands">True · Perlick · Turbo Air · U-Line · Marvel</p>
      </div>
      <div class="equip-card">
        <div class="equip-icon">🍽️</div>
        <h3>Glasswashers & Bar Dishwashers</h3>
        <p>Undercounter glasswashers, pass-through models. Temperature failures, pump issues, wash arm blockages, door gaskets. LADPH rinse temperature documentation.</p>
        <p class="equip-brands">Champion · Jackson · Hobart · Winterhalter</p>
      </div>
      <div class="equip-card">
        <div class="equip-icon">🌡️</div>
        <h3>Walk-In Beer Coolers</h3>
        <p>Walk-in cooler temperature failures, fan motor issues, evaporator problems. A walk-in beer cooler failure before a weekend is a priority dispatch call.</p>
        <p class="equip-brands">Norlake · True · Kolpak · Heatcraft</p>
      </div>
      <div class="equip-card">
        <div class="equip-icon">🍲</div>
        <h3>Back-of-House Kitchen (Bar Food)</h3>
        <p>Many LA bars serve food — flat-top grills, fryers, small commercial ranges. We cover back-of-house kitchen equipment for bars with full or limited food programs.</p>
        <p class="equip-brands">Vulcan · Garland · Pitco · American Range</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="context-grid">
      <div class="context-text">
        <p class="sl">Los Angeles Bar & Nightlife Context</p>
        <h2>WeHo, DTLA, Silver Lake — LA's bar landscape runs equipment hard</h2>
        <p>West Hollywood's bar mile along Santa Monica Boulevard is one of the densest concentrations of bars in any neighborhood in the US. These venues run equipment seven nights a week with high volume, late hours, and minimal maintenance windows. A Perlick keg cooler in a WeHo bar might run continuously for 18 months before anyone thinks about preventive maintenance.</p>
        <p>Downtown LA's arts and entertainment district has a different profile — larger venues, craft cocktail programs with serious ice requirements, more elaborate back bar setups. The Scotsman or Manitowoc ice machines in DTLA cocktail bars are often producing specialized ice — large format cubes, crushed — and failing outside of standard parameters.</p>
        <p>Silver Lake and Echo Park bars tend to be smaller, independently owned, with tighter margins and equipment that's often older. A repair that makes economic sense is especially important here. We give straight answers on repair vs. replacement.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="facts">
        <div class="fact">
          <h4>🍸 WeHo — highest bar density in LA</h4>
          <p>West Hollywood's Santa Monica Boulevard corridor has more bars per block than almost anywhere in LA. Equipment runs hard, hours are long, margins are tight.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="fact">
          <h4>💧 LA hard water kills ice machines</h4>
          <p>300–400 mg/L TDS. Scale buildup in ice machines reduces production capacity by 30–50% before most operators notice. Quarterly descaling is not optional in LA.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="fact">
          <h4>🎤 Event-driven urgency</h4>
          <p>Private events, DJ nights, industry parties — LA bars have high-stakes weekends where equipment failures have a direct, large dollar amount attached to them.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="fact">
          <h4>🌙 Late service hours</h4>
          <p>Bars that close at 2am can't do maintenance during service hours. Morning calls are the window. We respond fast to morning bar calls because we know why they're calling then.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">Recent Jobs</p>
    <h2>What bar service calls look like in LA</h2>
    <div class="jobs-grid">
      <div class="job-card">
        <span class="job-tag">Cocktail Bar, West Hollywood</span>
        <h3>"Ice machine making half what it should — Friday morning"</h3>
        <p>Called at 8am Friday. Manitowoc ice machine at 40% production capacity. LA hard water scale had built up in the water distribution system — heavy enough to cut production nearly in half. Descaled the evaporator and water circuits, ran a cleaning cycle, confirmed full production. Bar had ice by 11am. Showed the bar manager the quarterly maintenance protocol.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="job-card">
        <span class="job-tag">Nightclub, Downtown LA</span>
        <h3>"Perlick keg cooler not holding temp — Saturday afternoon"</h3>
        <p>Keg cooler drifting up to 48°F. Called Saturday at 2pm. Evaporator fan motor failure on a Perlick draft system. Our tech had the motor in stock — Perlick fan motors are common parts. Running at 34°F by 5pm. Club opened on time. Manager said a previous service company had told him he needed a new unit.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="job-card">
        <span class="job-tag">Wine Bar, Silver Lake</span>
        <h3>"Back bar wine display not cooling — bottles at 65°F"</h3>
        <p>True wine display case with a failed thermostat. 60 bottles of by-the-glass wine at ambient temperature. Replaced the thermostat, confirmed compressor was fine, verified temp stabilizing at 54°F before leaving. Owner had been worried it was the compressor — thermostat was a fraction of the cost. Honest diagnosis matters.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="job-card">
        <span class="job-tag">Bar & Kitchen, Echo Park</span>
        <h3>"Glasswasher not reaching rinse temperature"</h3>
        <p>Champion undercounter glasswasher failing health department rinse temperature requirement. Heating element scaled from LA hard water — common in bars that don't descale regularly. Replaced the element and descaled the unit. Manager got documentation for the health inspector. Also set up a quarterly descaling reminder.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">Why Same Day Appliance Repair</p>
    <h2>Why LA bars call us</h2>
    <div class="why-grid">
      <div class="why-card">
        <div class="why-icon">⚡</div>
        <h3>Friday morning calls get priority</h3>
        <p>We know what day of the week it is and what's at stake. A Friday morning bar call goes to the front of our dispatch queue — not because we're nice, but because the math is obvious.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-card">
        <div class="why-icon">🧊</div>
        <h3>Ice machine parts on the truck</h3>
        <p>Manitowoc, Hoshizaki, Scotsman — we stock the water valves, harvest controls, and evaporator components that fail most often in LA bar ice machines. Most calls get resolved same visit.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-card">
